Class EditorModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.EditorModel

  • public class EditorModel
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for all activities related to level editor. It stores all bricks for currently chosen level in a list - editorObjects.
    Author:
    Antek

      • processClick

        public java.awt.Point processClick(java.awt.event.MouseEvent me)
        Method to process mouse clicks. Its task is to decide whether user can create/delete Brick in place specified by MouseEvent me passed to it or not. If user clicked inside of editor board, funtion returs Point with x and y values corresponding x and y of Brick which would lay there.
        Parameters:
        me - - MouseEvent with useful information
        Returns:
        Point, if user clicked inside editor area, null otherwise

      • createStillObject

        public StillObject createStillObject(java.awt.Point coordinates)
        Creates StillObject using passed coordinates (if it is not null). The number of brick's HPs (and its color) depends on actual value of field brickHealth. *
        Parameters:
        coordinates - of new Object
        Returns:
        new StillObject, if passed Point is not null and null otherwise.

      • addStillObject

        public boolean addStillObject(java.awt.event.MouseEvent me)
        Tries to create StillObject using passed MouseEvent as parameter. If it ends with success and there is no the same object in the editorObjects, this object is added to the editorObjects list.
        Parameters:
        me - - MouseEvent to process
        Returns:
        true, if function managed to add StillObject to editorObjects, false otherwise.

      • deleteStillObject

        public boolean deleteStillObject(java.awt.event.MouseEvent me)
        Tries to create StillObject using passed MouseEvent as parameter. If it ends with success and there is such an object in the editorObjects, this object is removed from the editorObjects.
        Parameters:
        me - - MouseEvent to process
        Returns:
        true, if function managed to remove StillObject from the editorObjects, false otherwise.

      • clearList

        public void clearList()
        Deletes all objects from editor's objects list (editorObjects) leaving only walls in the list.

      • makeFull

        public void makeFull()
        Clears the editorObjects, fill it with new objects until there is no free space on editor board.

      • saveLevel

        public boolean saveLevel(int level)
        Orders FileManaager to save actual list (editorObjects) as a level with number passed as a parameter.
        Parameters:
        level - number of level to save
        Returns:
        true, if number of levels has changed.

      • loadEditorLevel

        selectedIndex - - selected index of combobox in view, posing as a number of level to load
